|--------|-----------|------------------|
| **Concurrency** | 1 issue at a time | N issues at once (limited by `config.concurrency`) |
| **Failure behavior** | Stops on first failure | Continues, collects all results |
| **Progress display** | Per-issue output, no heartbeat | Live progress line, 60s heartbeat, per-phase callbacks |
| **Batching support** | Via batch loop (lines 614-648) | Not applicable |
| **Chain mode** | Supported, creates dependency chain | Not supported (forced to `false`) |
| **QA gate** | Pauses chain on QA failure (lines 700-730) | Not applicable |
| **Console output** | Enabled (`config.parallel = false`) | Suppressed (`config.parallel = true`) |
| **Promise handling** | `await` within loop | `Promise.allSettled()` with pLimit |
| **Pre-PR rebase** | Only on last issue in chain | Never triggered |

### 10. **Batch Execution Wrapper**

**Location:** `/Users/tony/Projects/sequant/src/lib/workflow/batch-executor.ts`, lines 349-412

The `executeBatch()` function wraps sequential issue execution within batch mode. It iterates through batches (lines 614-648 in run.ts), calling `executeBatch()` for each. Batches themselves run sequentially, but issues within a batch can run based on the mode.

